---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Project"
  description="Overview of The Compositional Bestiary project: six-hundred-year lineage, core commitments, and research roadmap."
  section="project"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <h1>The Project</h1>
    <p class="page-hero-sub">Conceptual overview, lineage, and commitments guiding the research.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section container prose">
    <h2>Six-Hundred-Year Lineage</h2>
    <p>The Compositional Bestiary traces an invisible thread through the history of composition pedagogy and imaginal technologyŌĆöfrom Guido d'Arezzo's invention of musical notation in the 11th century, through Athanasius Kircher's <em>Musurgia Universalis</em> and his legendary <em>Arca Musarithmica</em> (a mechanical system for composition by moving wooden rods), to contemporary AI-assisted composition tools.</p>
    <p>Each of these moments represents a different answer to the same fundamental question: <strong>How can we cultivate the inner capacities that enable beautiful music to emerge?</strong> How can techjique become a servant to inspiration rather than its obstacle?</p>
    <p>This project argues that algorithmic composition, properly understood through historical, imaginative, and spiritual frameworks, is not the death of musical creativity but its renewalŌĆöa return to older technologies of inner listening.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Three Core Commitments</h2>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Learning as Adventure</h4>
          <p>We approach composition not as a system to master, but as a landscape to explore. Each creature in the bestiary is an invitation to discover new compositional territories, to play, to fail, to imagine.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Personhood as Sacred</h4>
          <p>The composer's subjective experienceŌĆötheir unique voice, embodied practice, inner listeningŌĆöis not something to transcend but to honor. Technology serves the person, never replaces them.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Technology as Companion</h4>
          <p>Tools are allies in creativity, not obstacles. From Kircher's ark to modern plugins, tech×éĒlogy can expand what we're capable of imagining, if designed with wisdom and care.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  
   5┘ection class="section container prose">
    <h2>Research Roadmap</h2>
    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-date">2022ŌĆō2023</div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>Pre-inscription</h3>
          <p>Conceptual development, literature review, and initial bestiary sketches. Establishing the theoretical framework and historical foundations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-date">2023ŌĆō2024</div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>Coursework & Fieldwork</h3>
          <p>Intensive doctoral seminars, theoretical deepening, and compositional practice. First major works completed (SEAWATER I & II). Initial plugin prototypes developed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-date">2024 ŌĆō2025</div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>Writing & Implementation</h3>
          <p>Thesis chapters drafted, creature library expanded, full plugin suite developed. Integration of all multimedia elements.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-date">2025ŌĆō2026</div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <h3>Defense & Publication</h3>
          <p>Thesis revision and defense. Publication of multimedia artifact. Presentation and dissemination of research outcomes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  
   5┘ection class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Navigation</h2>
      <p>For deeper scholarly detail, visit <a href={`${base}research/`}>Research</a>. For compositional output, see <a href={`${base}works/`}>Works</a>. For interactive tools, explore <a href={`${base}tools/`}>Tools</a>. For the completed artifact, see <a href={`${base}book/`}>The Book</a>.</p>
